The paper presents a new genetic algorithm approach for optimization problems, which is likely to fall under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG) concepts in the proposed approach. Additionally, the paper introduces a new symbiotic approach (cs.SY) for the genetic algorithm, which is a unique feature of the paper. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.NE and cs.AI, followed by cs.GT, cs.LG, and cs.SY.
